ECON 3305 - Comparative Economic Systems
A survey of historical and contemporary methods of organizing a
society's economic activity. The basic nature and ideology of capitalism
and socialism are examined through case studies. Special attention is
given to the current U.S., Russian, Chinese, and Japanese economies.
Also recommended for majors in political science, social sciences,
history and other non-business fields. Students may not receive credit for
both ECON 2305 and 3305.
